		<!-- message -->
		<div>Chapter 4: Cont'd<br />
<br />
“There’s someone in the water over here!” Relik shouted to a nearby member of the ship’s crew. <br />
<br />
Torches were quickly brought over and those standing by the railing could see a small figure trying to swim to the ship. The crew sprung into action and in short order the shivering, frightened young woman was safe on the deck. She was wrapped in blankets and was given a mug of steaming tea to chase away the chill. <br />
<br />
After giving the girl a moment to calm herself, Erissa approached and kindly asked, “What is your name, my dear, and how did you come to be in the water so far from shore?” <br />
<br />
“I am Antinime and…..” She broke off and began to sob inconsolably. “They are dead, all dead!” she moaned. “All my fellow sisters, gone!” <br />
<br />
Everyone exchanged looks of shock and disbelief. Erissa wrapped her arms comfortingly around the distraught girl, letting her cry. When Antinime seemed to have her grief in check again, Erissa spoke to her gently, “It may be difficult to talk about, but please, tell us what happened.” <br />
<br />
Antinime looked up angrily. “It was the specters!” she hissed. &quot;Normally we would have seen them coming but for some reason they just seemed to materialize right in the middle of our flaming island!&quot; <br />
<br />
Tears streamed down Antinime's face. The pain of loss was readily apparent on her face. She suffered greatly. <br />
<br />
&quot;Is there any chance that there are any survivors?&quot; Lady Erissa stated simply. The sobs of the Sister slowed for a moment only to answer grimly. <br />
<br />
&quot;No, milady. I saw the vermin die.&quot; <br />
<br />
&quot;Your pardon?&quot; said Erissa &quot;What did you just call your sisters?&quot; The crying and moaning stopped. Relik got his first chance to look into the eyes of the small woman from the Sister Island. They were indigo. <br />
<br />
&quot;TIER'DAL!&quot; screamed Relik, as his blades seemed to materialize in his hands. The barbarian charged the woman still sitting on the deck. <br />
<br />
A flash of colors burst in front of his eyes and Relik spun backwards unable to gather his thoughts for a moment. The sounds of battle seemed distant. Momentarily stunned Relik stood up once more only to notice the crewman in front of him get tossed up hundreds of feet into the air, falling in the ocean behind the swiftly moving vessel. <br />
<br />
&quot;BLOODY ENCHANTER! SHE'S GOT AERIC!&quot; shouted one of the crewmen. His face quickly contorted into a vision of pain as another crewman stabbed him in the back with a knife. <br />
<br />
&quot;Don't kill him! He's been charmed, he can't control his actions!&quot; shouted Lady Erissa over the sounds of the fray. The crowd on the deck shifted and more crewmen were flung into the ocean. Relik finally caught a view of the Tier'dal causing the problems. Spells and arrows shot their way to her but she took little damage from them. Bodies were flung from the deck man at a time. The shouts and screams of the battle seemed to ring in Relik's ears. <br />
<br />
No more pain. <br />
No more evil... <br />
<br />
The sounds of the battle faded in and out of his mind. All went quiet. Images flashed before the Barbarians eyes. <br />
<br />
flicker <br />
<br />
Men clawing at their faces, blood streaming from the gashes they tore. <br />
<br />
flicker <br />
<br />
Women crying at a funeral in Freeport. Small children sobbing... <br />
<br />
flicker <br />
<br />
Houses burning in the commonlands, no.. all across Norrath... <br />
<br />
flicker flicker <br />
<br />
Endless fields of bone, ravens soaring across the sky, carrion eaters pick at the rotting flesh that still remained on the bones.. <br />
<br />
flicker flicker flickerflickerflicker <br />
<br />
too much pain.. <br />
<br />
flicker <br />
<br />
&quot;EEENNNOUUUGHHHH!!!&quot; The Warrior's words seemed to boom and echo across the water. Waves thrashed violently away from the large ship, the center of the storm. Dark clouds formed instantly in the sky. Lightning flickered and thunder clapped. <br />
<br />
&quot;no more pain...&quot; Relik said quietly to himself.</div>
